import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest

plt.legend()
plt.title("Anomalous Visit Durations by Department")

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from datetime import datetime

df = dataset.copy()
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()

# Convert to correct types
df[''DurationMinutes''] = pd.to_numeric(df[''DurationMinutes''], errors=''coerce'')
df[''BillingAmount''] = pd.to_numeric(df[''BillingAmount''], errors=''coerce'')
df[''DateOfBirth''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''DateOfBirth''], errors=''coerce'')

# Calculate patient age
today = pd.Timestamp(''now'')
df[''Age''] = df[''DateOfBirth''].apply(lambda dob: (today - dob).days // 365 if pd.notnull(dob) else None)

# Drop rows with missing data
df = df.dropna(subset=[''DoctorID'', ''PatientID'', ''DurationMinutes'', ''BillingAmount'', ''Age'', ''Department''])

# Aggregate by doctor
agg = df.groupby([''DoctorID'', ''Department'']).agg({
    ''DurationMinutes'': ''mean'',
    ''BillingAmount'': ''mean'',
    ''Age'': ''mean''
}).reset_index()

# Rename for clarity
agg.rename(columns={
    ''DurationMinutes'': ''AvgDuration'',
    ''BillingAmount'': ''AvgBilling'',
    ''Age'': ''AvgPatientAge''
}, inplace=True)

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.scatterplot(
    data=agg,
    x=''AvgPatientAge'',
    y=''AvgDuration'',
    size=''AvgBilling'',
    hue=''Department'',
    sizes=(50, 1000),
    alpha=0.7,
    edgecolor=''black'',
    palette=''Set2''
)

plt.title("Doctor Efficiency vs Patient Age vs Billing Impact")
plt.xlabel("Average Patient Age")
plt.ylabel("Average Visit Duration (minutes)")
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=''upper left'')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import zscore

df = dataset.copy()
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()
df[''TestDate''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''TestDate''], errors=''coerce'')
df = df.dropna(subset=[''TestDate'', ''TestType''])

# Daily test count
df[''TestDate''] = df[''TestDate''].dt.date
daily_counts = df.groupby([''TestDate'', ''TestType'']).size().reset_index(name=''TestCount'')

# Z-score to detect spikes
daily_counts[''ZScore''] = daily_counts.groupby(''TestType'')[''TestCount''].transform(lambda x: zscore(x, ddof=0))
daily_counts[''Anomaly''] = daily_counts[''ZScore''].abs() > 2.5

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
for test_type in daily_counts[''TestType''].unique():
    temp = daily_counts[daily_counts[''TestType''] == test_type]
    plt.plot(temp[''TestDate''], temp[''TestCount''], label=f"{test_type}", alpha=0.5)
    spikes = temp[temp[''Anomaly'']]
    plt.scatter(spikes[''TestDate''], spikes[''TestCount''], color=''red'', label=f"Spike: {test_type}")

plt.legend()
plt.title("Diagnostic Test Load Anomalies")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Test Volume")

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest

# Work with the Power BI dataset
df = dataset.copy()
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()  # Clean column names

# Rename if Power BI used spaces
if ''Test Date'' in df.columns:
    df.rename(columns={''Test Date'': ''TestDate''}, inplace=True)
if ''Turnaround Hours'' in df.columns:
    df.rename(columns={''Turnaround Hours'': ''TurnaroundHours''}, inplace=True)

# Ensure correct types
df[''TestDate''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''TestDate''], errors=''coerce'')
df[''TurnaroundHours''] = pd.to_numeric(df[''TurnaroundHours''], errors=''coerce'')
df = df.dropna(subset=[''TestDate'', ''TurnaroundHours''])

# If no data after cleaning, show fallback plot
if df.empty:
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 2))
    plt.text(0.5, 0.5, ''No data available'', ha=''center'', va=''center'', fontsize=12)
    plt.axis(''off'')
    plt.title(''Anomaly Detection Result'')
    plt.show()
else:
    # Anomaly detection
    model = IsolationForest(contamination=0.05, random_state=42)
    df[''anomaly''] = model.fit_predict(df[[''TurnaroundHours'']])

    # Plot results
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
    plt.plot(df[''TestDate''], df[''TurnaroundHours''], label=''Normal'', alpha=0.5)
    plt.scatter(df[df[''anomaly''] == -1][''TestDate''], df[df[''anomaly''] == -1][''TurnaroundHours''],
                color=''red'', label=''Anomalies'')
    plt.title(''Anomaly Detection: Turnaround Hours'')
    plt.xlabel(''Test Date'')
    plt.ylabel(''Turnaround Hours'')
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
